The paper deals with video segmentation, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). It also involves the use of image graphs and fuzzy object models, which are techniques commonly used in multimedia processing (cs.MM) and graph theory (cs.GR). The method presented in the paper is interactive and involves user input, which suggests the use of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques to improve the segmentation process.
